        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): apply output text transforms to toolcall_delta and toolcall_end events",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`toolcall_delta` and `toolcall_end` stream events bypass the output text replacement pipeline. When plugin `textTransforms` mask PII tokens (e.g. `\"John Smith\"` → `\"[PER_001]\"`), the LLM generates tool calls using the masked tokens. Since these event types aren't processed, the masked tokens leak into tool arguments and external systems (Slack, email, etc.).\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`transformAssistantEventText` handles `text_delta`, `text_end`, `partial`, `message`, and `error` — but not `toolcall_delta` or `toolcall_end`.\n\n## Fix\n\nAdd `toolcall_delta` to the delta replacement path (same as `text_delta`) and add `toolcall_end` handling via a new `transformToolCallText` helper.\n\nCloses #97761\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n## Scope\n\n- [x] Agents (plugin text transform pipeline)\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Test**: Output replacements now apply to tool call events:\n- `toolcall_delta` with `[MASKED]` in delta text → restored to `\"John\"`\n- `toolcall_end` with `[MASKED]` in tool call name → restored to `\"John_greet\"`\n\n**Existing tests**: All text transform tests continue to pass.\n\n## Security Impact\n\n- New permissions? No\n- Secrets handling changed? No\n- New network calls? No\n",
        "branch": "fix/97761-toolcall-text-transforms",
